last_episode_to_air.name: Scotland
last_episode_to_air.overview: Phil sips a famed Scotch whisky on the Isle of Skye. In Edinburgh, he scarfs sweets, devours haggis and dines with award-winning actor Kelly Macdonald.

name: Somebody Feed Phil
overview: "Everybody Loves Raymond" creator Phil Rosenthal travels the globe to take in the local cuisine and culture of Bangkok, Lisbon, Mexico City and more.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: Globe-trotting gourmand Phil Rosenthal samples and savors culinary delights from Dubai, Edinburgh, Kyoto and more.

tagline: Get a taste of the world.

episodes.name: Bangkok
episodes.overview: Phil tours a floating market by boat, samples the world's best street food in Chinatown and takes on a 25-course tasting menu with a futuristic twist.

episodes.name: Saigon
episodes.overview: A tasty trip to Saigon kicks off with pho and banh mi. Phil gets up at dawn to harvest lotus stems and learns how real Vietnamese coffee is made.

episodes.name: Tel Aviv
episodes.overview: In vibrant Tel Aviv, Phil reconnects with old friends over shakshuka, visits a synagogue-themed hummus shop and meets "the princess of soup."

episodes.name: Lisbon
episodes.overview: Phil savors Lisbon's famed pasteis de nata tarts, tours the city in a motorcycle sidecar and dines with a chef at his Michelin-starred restaurant.

episodes.name: New Orleans
episodes.overview: Phil learns how to eat crawfish, goes hog-wild at a butcher shop and meets up with friends for a Monday night tradition: red beans and rice.

episodes.name: Mexico City
episodes.overview: After a mezcal-soaked meal, Phil tries his hand at tortilla making and introduces a stranger to the wonders of tacos al pastor.

episodes.name: Venice
episodes.overview: In Italy, Phil devours a sublime pork chop, pilots a gondola, dines with a famous chef, and marvels over gelato, aged cheese and balsamic vinegar.

episodes.name: Dublin
episodes.overview: With wife Monica along to trace her Irish roots, Phil feasts on boxty and seaweed, warily plays beekeeper, and learns how to pour and drink Guinness.

episodes.name: Buenos Aires
episodes.overview: Argentina delights Phil as he swoons over dulce de leche delicacies, wild boar choripán and divine cuts of beef. Bonus: He tangos and rides a horse.

episodes.name: Copenhagen
episodes.overview: Phil relishes new interpretations of Nordic classics such as smørrebrød and frikadeller before joining his family for fun and games at Tivoli Gardens.

episodes.name: Cape Town
episodes.overview: Phil gamely tries ostrich and antelope, eats with Nelson Mandela's grandson, tucks into BBQ and a family meal, and taste-tests coffee and flowers.

episodes.name: New York City
episodes.overview: Steak. Pizza. Hot dogs. Egg creams. Fall in love with Phil's New York as he noshes with friends Al Roker, Judy Gold, Elaine May and Tracy Morgan.

episodes.name: Marrakesh
episodes.overview: The warmest of welcomes greets Phil in Morocco, where he savors lamb, gets a pop quiz on spices and commits a couscous faux pas over a family dinner.

episodes.name: Chicago
episodes.overview: With daughter Lily in tow, Phil gives his arteries a workout by devouring deep-fried hot dogs, delicious pie and, of course, deep-dish pizza.

episodes.name: London
episodes.overview: Breaking bread with friends old and new, Phil indulges in gustatory delights ranging from a simple meal of fish and chips to a posh venison nosh.

episodes.name: Seoul
episodes.overview: A fan of the Korean food in LA, Phil eagerly heads to the source to try tteokbokki, feast on crab and gobble fried chicken with K-pop star Eric Nam.

episodes.name: Montreal
episodes.overview: Phil experiences the diverse city by munching on mind-blowing bagels and chicken, dining with a cheeky chef and pigging out on a wildly decadent meal.

episodes.name: Rio de Janeiro
episodes.overview: Phil feels the beat — and heat — while dancing at Carnival, sampling fruit and feijoada, sipping potent caipirinhas and pigging out at a churrascaria.

episodes.name: San Francisco
episodes.overview: In one of his favorite cities, Phil savors chocolate croissants, queasily sails the bay and visits with culinary icons Alice Waters and Thomas Keller.

episodes.name: Singapore
episodes.overview: Mouthwatering fare from the hawker markets delights Phil, who also digs into a to-die-for Peranakan meal and admires the area's stunning architecture.

episodes.name: The Mississippi Delta
episodes.overview: Phil soaks up the Southern scenery — and plenty of barbecue sauce — as he munches on ribs, fried lobster, hot tamales, alligator and a slab of steak.

episodes.name: Hawaii
episodes.overview: Exploring the aloha spirit on the beaches and beyond, Phil enjoys poke, shave ice, huli huli chicken, poi and — gasp — even a few outdoor adventures.

episodes.name: Oaxaca
episodes.overview: Phil enjoys mole, memelas, mezcal and a worm salad on a visit to the vibrant food capital, where he also shares chicharrones with actor Jimmi Simpson.

episodes.name: Maine
episodes.overview: Phil's two main reasons for loving this destination? Lobster and family. He feasts on butter-drenched lobster rolls before visiting his cousins' farm.

episodes.name: Helsinki
episodes.overview: Phil finds a warm welcome in Finland as he eats a tasty meal in a sauna, goes fishing and tries muikku, reindeer, vorschmack, and coffee with cheese.

episodes.name: Portland
episodes.overview: Phil digs into the eclectic fare from the Pacific Northwest city's bustling food truck scene and gets salty with "Top Chef" favorite Shota Nakajima.

episodes.name: Madrid
episodes.overview: Tortillas, tapas, heaps of jamón and a side trip to picturesque Toledo are among the highlights from Phil's memorable first visit to Spain's capital.

episodes.name: Philadelphia
episodes.overview: The City of Brotherly Love opens its arms to Phil as he digs into iconic sandwiches, breaks bread with pal Patton Oswalt and samples new Philly classics.

episodes.name: Croatia
episodes.overview: Phil island-hops in Croatia, where he dons a snorkel and has a run-in with sea urchins, feasts on fresh seafood and enjoys a happy dance-inducing gelato.

episodes.name: Austin
episodes.overview: Barbecue is an art in Austin — and Phil's happy to taste new variations. He also noshes with the Taco Mafia and takes a spin in a Formula One race car.

episodes.name: Santiago
episodes.overview: Against the backdrop of the Andes, Phil goes on a sánguche crawl in Santiago, Chile, where a sandwich is elevated to a fork-and-knife experience.

episodes.name: Nashville
episodes.overview: Phil eats to the Nashville beat as he discovers red-eye gravy, challenges son Ben to a spicy chicken-eating contest and visits with famous local legends.

episodes.name: Tribute to Helen and Max
episodes.overview: Phil pays homage to his beloved parents, Helen and Max, whose warm humor brightened the show and inspired him as the creator of "Everyone Loves Raymond."

episodes.name: Mumbai
episodes.overview: After a tasty tour of Mumbai's bustling street food scene, Phil joins dabbawalas in delivering meals. A legendary chef is honored at The Bombay Canteen.

episodes.name: Washington, D.C.
episodes.overview: After enjoying an epic chili dog, Phil does an intense rowing workout and meets members of Washington D.C.'s Deaf community who run a popular pizzeria.

episodes.name: Kyoto
episodes.overview: Kyoto's artful approach to dining makes Phil hungry for more as he slurps soba, meets an omurice virtuoso and wanders a market beloved by foodies.

episodes.name: Iceland
episodes.overview: Iceland's natural beauty dazzles Phil, who visits a popular bakery and chomps on street hot dogs — but is not so keen on taking a dip in icy-cold waters.

episodes.name: Dubai
episodes.overview: Cultures converge in Dubai, home to what Phil calls the "best burger ever." He also visits a traditional teahouse and sits in on a Ramadan iftar.

episodes.name: "The Real" Orlando
episodes.overview: Look beyond the theme parks to find Orlando's diverse food scene, where Phil digs into porchetta, Filipino ice cream and paella — plus a hefty cookie.

episodes.name: Taipei
episodes.overview: Phil licks his plate after an amazing meal in Taipei, savors the tantalizing aromas of Jiufen Old Street and dines with NBA star Dwight Howard.

episodes.name: Scotland
episodes.overview: Phil sips a famed Scotch whisky on the Isle of Skye. In Edinburgh, he scarfs sweets, devours haggis and dines with award-winning actor Kelly Macdonald.

7.name: Season 7
7.overview: Globe-trotting gourmand Phil Rosenthal samples and savors culinary delights from Dubai, Edinburgh, Kyoto and more.
